PN,44904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1773280992
OL,3,CEarly referral of Noah case to
OL,4,Cspecialist unit 'unusual but justified'
OL,6,FMr Lunney asked if at the point of
OL,7,Fhandover officers were taking time to
OL,8,Ffamiliarise themselves with the case,
OL,9,Fto which Mr Robinson said "in regards
OL,10,Fto risk assessment, yes" but that
OL,11,Fthese should have been recorded in a
OL,12,Fseparate tab elsewhere than the
OL,13,Finvestigative log.
OL,15,FAsked if he had any concerns about the
OL,16,Fcontinuity of the investigation, Mr
OL,17,FRobinson said he did not in regards to
OL,18,Fhandover and awareness of Noah's high-
OL,19,Frisk status, but that the rationale
OL,20,Ffor his status of high-risk had not
OL,21,Fbeen logged.
OL,26,@qD@[OUrD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/7
