PN,44906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F449A1773280992
OL,3,CEarly referral of Noah case to
OL,4,Cspecialist unit 'unusual but justified'
OL,6,FMr Robinson further stated that "time
OL,7,Fin a missing person case is not the
OL,8,Fonly factor" and that other factors
OL,9,Fsuch as risk of criminal involvement
OL,10,Fcan cause a cause to be elevated to
OL,11,FCID.
OL,13,FThe court was shown a statement from
OL,14,Fhis "compliance review" into the PSNI
OL,15,Fhandling of the case where Mr Robinson
OL,16,Fstated: "In my experience this case
OL,17,Fpassed to CID at a very early stage",
OL,18,Fadding that in his time as detective
OL,19,Finspector he had "never" referred a
OL,20,Fcase to CID.
OL,26,@nD@aOUpD@LO]vD@EOUvD@WO]xD@IOUyD@dO]{D@
OL,26,AROU{D@XO]
